```
On the Storage account, create a folder mnt (if you haven't done so in 01_Delta_Lake_Getting_started notebook). 
Create a folder datasets. 
Upload the file diamonds.csv ( available in "datasets" folder in this IP artifact) into /mnt/datasets

```
Using spark to read csv and write to delta lake

```
Reading the delta lake table written using scala from spark sql

```
using sparksql to read csv and load into delta table

%%sql
-- mode "FAILFAST" will abort file parsing with a RuntimeException if any malformed lines are encountered
CREATE OR REPLACE TEMPORARY VIEW diamonds_vw
USING CSV
OPTIONS (path "/mnt/datasets/diamonds.csv", header "true", mode "FAILFAST")

%%sql
DROP TABLE if exists db1.diamonds_sql;
CREATE OR REPLACE TABLE db1.diamonds_sql 
USING DELTA
LOCATION '/mnt/datasets/diamonds'
AS
Select * from diamonds_vw
Using sparksql to create table in delta database stored using csv files

%%sql
DROP TABLE if exists db1.diamonds_csv;
CREATE TABLE db1.diamonds_csv 
USING CSV
LOCATION '/mnt/datasets/diamonds_csv'
AS
Select * from diamonds_vw
Reading delta table stored as csv using spark
Insert into db1.diamonds_csv select * from db1.diamonds_csv
Update db1.diamonds_sql SET color = 'Y' where color = 'E'
